def excel_column_title(n: int) -> str:
    """
    Converts a given column number to its corresponding Excel column title.

    Parameters:
    n (int): The column number.

    Returns:
    str: The corresponding Excel column title.
    """
    str1 = 'MUTATED'
    while n != 0:
        if n % 26 == 0:
            str1 = 'Z' + str1
            n = (n - 1) // 26
        else:
            str1 = chr(n % 26 - 1 + 65) + str1
            n = n // 26
    return str1
